  "text": "Seized samples containing furanylfentanyl, carfentanil and U-47700 were quantified by the caffeine-calibrated LC-CLND method described above. These drugs were identified by high resolution mass spectrometry and, initially by NMR spectroscopy, without other illicit drug findings prior to submitting the samples for quantification by LC-CLND. However, the DAD signal was used to assess the peak purity for CLND calculations, applying a DAD peak purity criterion of 99% as well as visual inspection. The expanded uncertainty of measurement, calculated as shown before [CITATION_1] , was always <20% as the systematic error component was low.",
